The paper focuses on Federated Learning (FL) which is a machine learning technique, indicating that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges of FL in wireless networks, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The paper proposes a resource allocation optimization problem, indicating that it could belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also discusses the convergence rate of the proposed algorithm, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper employs the proposed algorithm in wireless networks, indicating that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
